Maybe an option here would be to emit the DWARF describing the vtable's type as a struct of structs, like
```
struct vtable_for_object {
    struct trait_one {
      void (*method)();
    } vtable_trait_one;
    struct trait_two {
      void (*method)();
    } vtable_trait_two;
};
```
This way the flattening is communicated directly.
